From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 18:25:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Camera/stagefright: Resolve video recording freezes and color
 casts

Implement a combined fix for the Snap camera app video recording stop freeze
and green color cast issues on devices utilizing legacy camera HAL wrappers:

1. libcameraservice: Relax client metadata buffer size validations
   - In api1/CameraClient and device1/CameraHardwareInterface, change strict
     size validations on incoming camera callback buffers from strict equality
     checks (`!=` / `== sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)`) to relational checks
     (`<` / `>=`).
   - This prevents the framework from dropping 20-byte legacy metadata buffers
     coming from custom HAL wrappers (containing indices and original FDs) and
     allows them to pass validation cleanly in metadata recording mode.

2. libstagefright: Prevent deadlocks during recording stop
   - In CameraSource::read(), return `ERROR_END_OF_STREAM` if the timeout guard
     waiting for incoming camera video frames (3 seconds) is tripped.
   - This ensures the video encoder and MPEG4Writer threads exit gracefully and
     break the read loop when the camera stop call is invoked, preventing system
     freezes and cameraserver deadlocks.

3. libstagefright: Correct color format configuration
   - In MediaCodecSource::initEncoder(), query and apply the color-format directly
     from the input/output format parameters when in metadata mode.
   - This prevents falling back to incompatible layouts, resolving the green
     video color cast.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.5 Flash (High)

